EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to trade regulations; setting forth certain
requirements and restrictions concerning certain inflatable
devices; requiring certain businesses that operate such
devices to meet certain requirements; setting forth
requirements for certain inspections of and warnings
relating to such devices; imposing certain restrictions on
the use of such devices under certain circumstances;
authorizing a county, city or town to enact certain
ordinances; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Sections 2-13 of this bill set forth certain requirements and restrictions
2 concerning inflatable devices and certain businesses that operate such devices.
3 Section 3 defines the term “inflatable device” to mean an air-filled device that: (1)
4 incorporates certain structural and mechanical elements to achieve its strength,
5 shape and stability by tensioning from internal air pressure; and (2) is intended for
6 use by a person to bounce, play, slide, climb or otherwise interact for outdoor
7 recreation, including a constant air inflatable bounce house, inflatable waterslide or
8 similar device. Section 5 defines the term “operator business” to mean a business
9 entity which is engaged in the business of making inflatable devices available for
10 use in this State and which employs, controls, directs or hires as an independent
11 contractor an operator to act on behalf of the business entity. Section 4 defines the
12 term “operator” to mean a person on-site at the location where an inflatable device
13 is used who sets up, operates, maintains or supervises the use of the inflatable
14 device on behalf of an operator business.
15 Section 6 prohibits a person from engaging in the business of an operator
16 business unless the person: (1) holds all applicable state and local business licenses;
