17 and (2) has obtained certain insurance or a surety bond in an amount of not less
18 than $1,000,000.
19 Section 7 requires an operator business to keep a logbook for any inflatable
20 device that is made available for use by the operator business, which must be kept
21 with the inflatable device and made available for inspection at the request of certain
22 persons and any state or local agency. Sections 7-11 require an operator, before and
23 during each use of an inflatable device, to conduct certain inspections of the device
24 and the area in which it will be used and to record and retain for not less than 2
25 years the results of those inspections and certain other information in the logbook.
26 Section 8 prohibits an operator from allowing any person to use the inflatable
27 device if an inspection reveals or would have revealed a hazard or potential hazard
28 that would make use of the inflatable device unsafe, according to the requirements
29 of this bill or the requirements or recommendations contained in any user manual
30 provided by the manufacturer of the inflatable device, any update to such a user
31 manual and any information relating to a recall of the inflatable device. Section 9
32 prohibits an operator from allowing a person to use an inflatable device if any label
33 attached by the manufacturer of the device is missing. Section 9 also prohibits an
34 operator business from selling or transferring an inflatable device if any such label
35 is missing or if any user manual provided by the manufacturer, any update to such a
36 user manual and any information relating to a recall of the inflatable device is not
37 provided to the seller or transferee. Section 10 requires an operator to: (1) monitor
38 wind speed at any location where an inflatable device will be used at all times while
39 the device is in use; and (2) cease operation of the inflatable device if the wind
40 speed exceeds the recommendation of the manufacturer or 15 miles per hour,
41 whichever is greater. Section 11 prescribes certain requirements for anchoring the
42 inflatable device to the ground.
43 Section 13.5 of this bill authorizes a county, city or town to enact an ordinance
44 which establishes requirements and restrictions which are the same as or in addition
45 to those set forth in this bill and which provides for the imposition of criminal or
46 civil penalties, or both, for violations of those requirements and restrictions.
