5 Sec. 3. “Inflatable device” means an air-filled device that:
6 1. Incorporates a structural and mechanical system and
7 employs a high-strength fabric or film that achieves its strength,
8 shape and stability by tensioning from internal air pressure;
9 2. Is intended for use by a person to bounce, play, slide, climb
10 or otherwise interact for outdoor recreation; and
11 3. Includes, without limitation, a constant air inflatable
12 bounce house, inflatable slide or water slide, obstacle course, pool
13 or enclosed inflatable trampoline.
14 Sec. 4. “Operator” means a person on-site at the location
15 where an inflatable device is used who sets up, operates, maintains
16 or supervises the use of the inflatable device on behalf of an
17 operator business.
18 Sec. 5. “Operator business” means a business entity,
19 including, without limitation, a sole proprietorship that:
20 1. Is engaged in the business of making inflatable devices
21 available for use in this State; and
22 2. Employs, controls, directs or hires as an independent
23 contractor an operator to act on behalf of the business entity.
24 Sec. 6. A person shall not engage in the business of an
25 operator business unless the person:
26 1. Holds all applicable state and local business licenses; and
27 2. Has obtained a liability insurance policy, or a certificate of
28 insurance thereof, or a bond of a surety company or other surety
29 in an amount not less than $1,000,000.
30 Sec. 7. 1. An operator business shall keep a logbook for
31 any inflatable device which is made available for use by the
32 operator business. The logbook may be written or electronic, but
33 must be available in a form that is kept with the inflatable device
34 at all times and must be available for inspection at the request of
35 any customer of the business, user of the inflatable device or any
36 state or local agency.
37 2. An operator shall record and retain for not less than 2
38 years the results of each inspection conducted pursuant to sections
39 8 to 11, inclusive, of this act in the logbook.
40 3. If an operator or operator business temporarily or
41 permanently discontinues the operation or use of an inflatable
42 device for any of the reasons described in sections 8 to 11,
43 inclusive, of this act, or described in any user manual provided by
44 the manufacturer of the inflatable device, the operator shall
45 record that information in the logbook.
