32 Sec. 10. 1. An operator shall not allow any person to use
33 an inflatable device at a location if the wind speed at the location
34 exceeds the greater of:
35 (a) The recommendation of the manufacturer for the specific
36 inflatable device in use; or
37 (b) Not more than 15 miles per hour.
38 2. The operator shall use an anemometer to measure the
39 wind speed, and record the wind speed in the logbook pursuant to
40 section 7 of this act before allowing any person to use the
41 inflatable device.
42 3. At all times while the inflatable device is in use, the
43 operator shall continue to monitor the wind speed at the location
44 by using an anemometer. If at any time during the use of the
45 device the wind speed exceeds the limits described in subsection 1,
