5 Sec. 11. 1. The operator shall ensure an inflatable device is
6 anchored to the ground before and at all times during the use of
7 the device.
8 2. To secure each point where the inflatable device is
9 anchored to the ground, the operator:
10 (a) Except as otherwise provided in paragraph (b), shall use:
11 (1) Stakes which are not less than 18 inches long and
12 which are driven into the ground at not less than a 22 degree
13 angle towards the center of the inflatable device, unless the
14 recommendations of the manufacturer for the specific device
15 require stakes which are longer; and
16 (2) Weights which are not less than 75 pounds per anchor
17 point, unless the recommendations of the manufacturer for the
18 specific device require a heavier weight.
19 (b) If the surface on which the inflatable device is to be used is
20 concrete, asphalt or another surface that cannot reasonably
21 accommodate the use of stakes as described in paragraph (a), may,
22 in lieu of stakes, use additional weights at each anchor point if:
23 (1) The amount of additional weight is reasonable under
24 the circumstances;
25 (2) The total weight used at each anchor point is greater
26 than the weight described in subparagraph (2) of paragraph (a);
27 and
28 (3) The operator records the circumstances and weight of
29 any additional weights so used in the logbook pursuant to section
30 7 of this act.
31 Sec. 12. An operator shall display in a conspicuous place in
32 front of an inflatable device at all times during the use of the
33 device, a legible and typewritten sign which is labeled
34 “OPERATOR’S WARNING” in red and in not less than 72-point
35 boldface type. The sign must be not less than 2 feet in length and
36 in width and must contain the following information, in a type and
37 font that is easy to read and in substantially the following form:
38 1. Use of an inflatable device can cause injury or death.
39 2. A logbook of safety inspections for this inflatable device is
40 available for review upon the request of any customer of the
41 business, user of the inflatable device or any state or local agency.
42 3. The maximum allowable wind speed for the safe operation
43 of an inflatable device is the greater of:
44 (a) The recommendation of the manufacturer of the inflatable
45 device; or
